Use the ROS Navigation Stack to complete autonomous navigation in the given map environment. Run the following three navigation configurations and compare their navigation performance:

1. Default global planner + DWA local planner
2. Default global planner + TEB local planner
3. A* global planner + TEB local planner

You need to run these configurations in both the simulation environment and on the LIMO vehicle. Use RViz 2D Nav Goal to assign navigation targets and record the navigation results.

Refer to:
https://github.com/Intelligent-Robot-Course/Intelligent-Robots-Lab/tree/main/LAB10
for more details.

A lab report is required, which should include but is not limited to the following aspects:

- Screenshots or videos of the navigation results for the three configurations.
- A brief comparison of their performance, such as path smoothness, navigation stability, obstacle avoidance behavior, and whether the robot can successfully reach the goal.
- A short explanation of the basic ideas of DWA, TEB, and A*/Dijkstra global planning.
- A brief discussion of the difference between simulation and LIMO vehicle results.
- Any parameter adjustments you made and how they affected the navigation behavior.
- Your conclusion and personal insights from this lab.
